      '\n> **Current**: This document describes video learning features in the MVP.\n\n# Video Learning\n\nAspiron\'s video learning system provides structured, interactive video content for effective learning.\n\n## Video Features\n\n### Playback Controls\n\n- **Playback Speed** - 0.5x to 2x speed control\n- **Resume** - Starts from where you left off\n- **Skip Forward/Back** - 10-second navigation\n- **Volume** - Standard volume control\n- **Fullscreen** - Immersive viewing\n\n### Video Navigation\n\n- **Progress Bar** - Visual progress indicator\n- **Chapter Markers** - Jump to specific sections\n- **Timeline Thumbnails** - Preview frames on hover\n- **Timestamps** - Click to jump to specific time\n\n### Bookmarks\n\n#### Create Bookmark\n\n- Click bookmark icon while watching\n- Add personal note to bookmark\n- Timestamp automatically saved\n\n#### Manage Bookmarks\n\n- View all bookmarks in sidebar\n- Click to jump to timestamp\n- Edit bookmark notes\n- Delete bookmarks\n\n### Video Transcript\n\n#### Transcript Features\n\n- **Searchable Text** - Find content within video\n- **Click to Jump** - Click text to jump to position\n- **AI Integration** - Transcript used for AI context\n- **Multi-language** - Transcript in selected language\n\n#### Transcript Panel\n\n- Toggle transcript panel\n- Scroll through transcript\n- Highlight current position\n- Copy text to notes\n\n## Video Organization\n\n### Topic Videos\n\nEach topic has associated videos:\n\n- **Primary Video** - Main explanation\n- **Supplementary Videos** - Additional examples\n- **Practice Videos** - Problem-solving walkthroughs\n\n### Video Playlists\n\nVideos are organized as:\n\n- Sequential playlists for chapters\n- Related video suggestions\n- Continue watching section\n- Up next recommendations\n\n## Video and Notes\n\n### Timestamped Notes\n\nCreate notes while watching:\n\n1. Click "Add Note" button\n2. Note is auto-timestamped\n3. Click timestamp to return to exact moment\n4. Notes linked to video and topic\n\n### Notes Integration\n\n- Notes appear in sidebar during playback\n- Click note to jump to video position\n- Notes sync with video progress\n- Reference specific video sections\n\n## Video and AI\n\n### AI Features\n\nAI enhances video learning:\n\n- **Transcript Analysis** - Indexes content for search\n- **Concept Explanations** - Explains complex parts\n- **Summary Generation** - Creates video summaries\n- **Related Suggestions** - Recommends related videos\n\n### AI Boundaries\n\nAI never:\n- Watches videos for you\n- Takes notes for you\n- Answers based on partial understanding\n\n## Video Quality\n\n### Quality Options\n\n- **Auto** - Based on connection\n- **1080p** - High definition\n- **720p** - Standard definition\n- **480p** - Low bandwidth\n\n### Offline Viewing\n\n> **Planned**: Offline download feature coming in later phases\n\n## Video Accessibility\n\n### Accessibility Features\n\n- **Keyboard Navigation** - Control playback with keyboard\n- **Screen Reader Support** - Transcript accessible\n- **Contrast Options** - High contrast mode (future)\n- **Captions** - Subtitles in supported languages\n\n---\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- [Live Classes](/docs/live-classes) - Learn about scheduled live sessions\n- [Teacher Notes](/docs/teacher-notes) - Explore official PDF notes\n- [Student Notes](/docs/student-notes) - Learn about timestamped notes\n- [Context-Aware AI Chat](/docs/context-ai-chat) - See AI video integration\n',
