    content:
      "\n> **Current**: This document describes the revision mode feature for focused review.\n\n# Revision Mode\n\nAspiron's revision mode provides a focused environment for reviewing mistakes and key content.\n\n## What Is Revision Mode\n\n### Definition\n\nA dedicated mode for:\n\n- Reviewing wrong answers\n- Memorizing formulas\n- Recalling key concepts\n- Quick access to resources\n\n### Access Points\n\nEnter revision mode from:\n\n- AI Recall Check results\n- Wrong questions list\n- Formula quick-reference\n- AI suggestions\n- Manual entry\n\n## Revision Features\n\n### Wrong Questions List\n\nShows all incorrectly answered questions:\n\n- From practice quizzes\n- From chapter tests\n- From mock exams\n- Organized by topic\n\nEach question shows:\n- Your answer\n- Correct answer\n- Explanation\n- Link to related content\n\n### Formula Review\n\nQuick reference for formulas:\n\n- By subject\n- By chapter\n- By topic\n- Searchable\n\nFeatures:\n- Formula statements\n- Variable meanings\n- Example applications\n- Related concepts\n\n### Key Points Summary\n\nAI-generated summaries:\n\n- Important concepts\n- Common mistakes\n- Quick reminders\n- Study tips\n\n### AI Summaries\n\nCombines:\n\n- Teacher notes highlights\n- Your notes summary\n- Key formulas\n- Important points\n\n## Revision Workflow\n\n### Identify Gaps\n\n1. Open revision mode\n2. Review wrong questions\n3. Note patterns\n4. Focus on weak areas\n\n### Targeted Review\n\n1. Click related video\n2. Read relevant notes\n3. Review formulas\n4. Take follow-up quiz\n\n### Track Improvement\n\n1. Re-attempt wrong questions\n2. See accuracy improvement\n3. Build confidence\n4. Reduce error rate\n\n## Revision Tools\n\n### Flashcards\n\n- Formula flashcards\n- Concept cards\n- Custom cards (future)\n- Spaced repetition (future)\n\n### Quick Links\n\n- Jump to video at timestamp\n- Open related notes\n- Start related quiz\n- Ask AI for explanation\n\n### Progress in Revision\n\n- Questions mastered\n- Topics reviewed\n- Time spent\n- Improvement over time\n\n## Revision and Context\n\n### Context-Aware\n\nRevision mode shows:\n\n- Relevant to your exam\n- Filtered by your subject\n- Targeted to your needs\n- Aligned with your goals\n\n### Personalized\n\nAI personalizes revision:\n\n- Focus on your weak areas\n- Skip what you know\n- Prioritize high-weight topics\n- Balance coverage\n\n---\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- [AI Recall Check](/docs/ai-recall-check) - See memory-aware revision\n- [Practice Quizzes](/docs/practice-quizzes) - Understand quizzes\n- [Test Analysis](/docs/test-analysis) - Learn about analysis\n- [Notes System](/docs/notes-system) - Explore notes integration\n",
