      '\n> **Core**: This document describes exam integrity and safety features.\n\n# Exam Integrity & Safety\n\nAspiron ensures exam integrity through technical safeguards and ethical principles.\n\n## Integrity Measures\n\n### AI Disable During Exams\n\nAI features are automatically disabled:\n\n- No AI chat during exams\n- No AI explanations during exams\n- No AI suggestions during exams\n- Pure student effort required\n\n### Copy/Paste Blocking\n\nDuring exams:\n\n- Copy functionality disabled\n- Paste functionality disabled\n- Right-click menu restricted\n- Keyboard shortcuts blocked\n\n### External Tools\n\nPrevention of:\n\n- Screen recording\n- External browsers\n- Chat applications\n- Answer sharing\n\n## Technical Safeguards\n\n### Exam Mode\n\nWhen taking exams:\n\n- Fullscreen required\n- Timer enforced\n- Navigation restricted\n- AI disabled\n\n### Proctoring Integration\n\nWorks with AI proctoring:\n\n- Focus score generation\n- Tab switch detection\n- Suspicious behavior flags\n- No real-time intervention\n\n## Student Transparency\n\n### Clear Communication\n\nStudents are informed:\n\n- "AI will be disabled during exam"\n- "Copy/paste is blocked"\n- "Your focus will be monitored"\n- "This is for your benefit"\n\n### No Surprises\n\nTransparency rules:\n\n- Clear before exam starts\n- Settings explained\n- Purpose stated\n- Questions answered\n\n## Integrity Boundaries\n\n### What Happens If...\n\n| Situation | Response |\n|-----------|----------|\n| Tab switch | Logged, not penalized |\n| Unusual pace | Flagged for self-awareness |\n| Focus issues | Reported to student only |\n| Suspicious patterns | Noted, no action in MVP |\n\n### MVP Approach\n\nTrust-first methodology:\n\n- No exam cancellation\n- No score reduction\n- No reporting to others\n- Only self-awareness tools\n\n### Future Considerations\n\n> **Planned**: May evolve based on feedback\n\n- Peer comparison (anonymous)\n- Achievement for integrity\n- Trust scores\n- Enhanced monitoring\n\n## Data and Privacy\n\n### What Is Monitored\n\nDuring exams:\n\n- Tab switching\n- Time on questions\n- Answer patterns\n- Focus duration\n\n### What Is NOT Monitored\n\nNever collected:\n\n- Screen content\n- Camera or microphone\n- Personal data\n- External communications\n\n### Data Usage\n\nMonitored data used for:\n\n- Focus score calculation\n- Integrity indicators\n- Personal improvement\n- NOT shared or sold\n\n## Student Rights\n\n### During Exam\n\nStudents have the right to:\n\n- Clear rules explained\n- Technical issues resolved\n- Fair assessment\n- Privacy protection\n\n### After Exam\n\nStudents can:\n\n- View focus score\n- See integrity report\n- Understand flagged behavior\n- Improve for next time\n\n---\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- [AI Proctoring](/docs/ai-proctoring) - Learn about proctoring features\n- [Tests & Mock Exams](/docs/tests-mock-exams) - Understand exam features\n- [Design Philosophy](/docs/design-philosophy) - See integrity philosophy\n- [Privacy By Design](/docs/design-philosophy) - Explore privacy principles\n',
